<topic id="author-docbook4-transformation-scenarios">
  <title>DocBook 4 Transformation Scenarios</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>DocBook 4</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DocBook 4 document type<indexterm>Transformation
          scenarios</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DocBook 4 transformations</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>Default transformation scenarios allow you to convert DocBook 4 to DocBook 5 documents and
      transform DocBook documents to a variety of outputs, such as WebHelp, PDF, HTML, HTML Chunk,
      XHTML, XHTML Chunk, and EPUB. All of them are listed in the <uicontrol>DocBook 4</uicontrol>
      section in the <xref
        href="configure-transformation-dialog.dita#configure-transformation-dialog"
          ><uicontrol>Configure Transformation Scenario(s)</uicontrol> dialog box</xref>.</p>
  </body>
